<P>I've verified that the rules are being run, and that what is called from the script is the same as what I type (with the exception of the back slash).&nbsp; But it doesn't work.</P>
<P>I suspect the problem is the "Macintosh-ness" of the computer, rather than your scripts and that this would work on a "normal" laptop.&nbsp; I'll come back if I figure it out.</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>For now I simply disable it by hand from a command prompt.&nbsp; I set couple of aliases that take the pain out.&nbsp; Which is not as nice, but better than nothing...<BR></P></p>
